Objective
│
├─ 1. Reconnaissance            — Learn without touching
│   ├─ Passive Recon           — No interaction
│   │   ├─ OSINT               — Public data
│   │   ├─ DNS records         — Infrastructure clues
│   │   └─ Certificate logs    — Hidden subdomains
│   │
│   └─ Active Recon            — Minimal interaction
│       ├─ ping                — Host alive
│       ├─ traceroute          — Network path
│       └─ HTTP probing        — Service presence
│
├─ 2. Asset Enumeration         — Define attack surface
│   ├─ IP ranges               — Network scope
│   ├─ Subdomains              — Entry points
│   ├─ Ports                   — Open doors
│   └─ Services                — What’s running
│
├─ 3. Surface Mapping           — Understand exposure
│   ├─ Web routes              — URLs & endpoints
│   ├─ APIs                    — Methods & schemas
│   ├─ Auth flows              — Login & tokens
│   └─ Third‑party services    — SaaS dependencies
│
├─ 4. Input Discovery           — Where data enters
│   ├─ Parameters              — Query / body fields
│   ├─ Headers                 — Trust boundaries
│   ├─ Cookies                 — Session control
│   └─ File uploads            — Binary input
│
├─ 5. Weakness Detection        — Find cracks
│   ├─ Misconfiguration        — Defaults, exposed panels
│   ├─ Known vulnerabilities   — CVEs
│   ├─ Logic flaws             — Broken workflows
│   └─ Access control gaps     — Missing authorization
│
├─ 6. Validation                — Is it real?
│   ├─ Proof of concept        — Minimal impact
│   ├─ Impact confirmation     — Data / control
│   └─ False‑positive removal  — Noise reduction
│
├─ 7. Exploitation (If any)     — Use the weakness
│   ├─ Privilege escalation    — More access
│   ├─ Lateral movement        — New assets
│   └─ Persistence             — Continued access
│
├─ 8. Post‑Exploitation         — Maximize value
│   ├─ Data access             — Sensitive info
│   ├─ Credential harvesting   — Reuse paths
│   └─ Infrastructure mapping  — Cloud / internal
│
├─ 9. Cover & Control           — Stay hidden
│   ├─ Noise reduction         — Slow & selective
│   ├─ Log evasion             — Blend with normal traffic
│   └─ Cleanup                 — Remove traces
│
└─ 10. Automation & Scaling     — Repeat efficiently
    ├─ Tool chaining           — Pipelines
    ├─ Templates               — Reusable logic
    └─ Continuous scanning     — New exposure

